Project Title: What’s Open Now? Android App
Date: February 9, 2012Prepared by: M. Bolaji, S. Cashin, M. Chien, K. McNamara & F. Zenteno
Project Description
The Android Application will be available for download from any of the group member’s machines and potentially the Android Application Market.  
Overall Objectives and Justification
The main objective of this project is to create a working Android application.  The application should be able in the very least to provide a list of operational hours for businesses and other places of interest in the specified locations.  The application, if completed, will be able to determine your location and notify you of the hours of operation for places around you.  This application will allow for users to save time trying to find the various hours of operation for places around UCI.
Detailed Description of Project Deliverables
We are creating an application, ‘What’s Open Now?’ for the Android platform.  The application will focus on three areas around UCI: the campus, University Town Center, and the shopping center near Albertson’s.  The application will also be able to tell you what is open around you based upon your phone’s GPS location, within a category of your choosing and time of access.
Characteristics & Requirements of Project Products and Services
The hours of operation, contact information, and locations provided should be current and accurate.  
Project Success Criteria
Test the accuracy of information given by the application to ensure accuracy.  Have the application contain enough locations for it to be useful and justifiable as a stand alone application.

What is Out of Scope
Everything that is outside of the locations mentioned: the UCI campus, Univeristy Town Center, and the shopping center off of the intersection of Campus Drive and California Avenue.  Basic contact information will be provided, but more information such as menus for restaurants is out of scope.  For the UCI campus, only eateries, libraries, Aldrich Hall, Zot-n-go, Zot Zone, Campus Police Center, Health Center, and the Visitor Center will be included.

Constraints/Assumptions
We are assuming that there is a need for this application.
We are constrained by the amount of time in this quarter and the lack of budget.

Project Title: What’s Open Now? Android App
Date: February 9, 2012Prepared by: M. Bolaji, S. Cashin, M. Chien, K. McNamara & F. Zenteno

Project Description
The application will contain useful and general contact information for many of the major facilities and restaurants available on the University of California, Irvine campus and in its surrounding area.  The information that the application will provide includes telephone number, addresses, and hours of operation. The application will also be able to detect the user’s geographic location and display the facilities that are currently open and near the user. The application will be made for the Android mobile platform. The application will be available for download from any of the group member and also the Android Application Market.

Overall Objectives and Justification
The main objective of this project is to create a working Android application that will help make the daily lives of the students at UCI easier. The application should be able to provide a the basic information for business and other places of interest on or near the UCI campus. The application will also be able to determine the user’s location through GPS and display a list of nearby places of interest as well as let the user know which of those places nearby are open at the moment. 

The University of California, Irvine’s campus and its surrounding areas contain many different facilities, from administration buildings, health centers, and counselling offices to cafeterias, parks, and restaurants. This application will be mainly targeted towards UCI students and will allow its users to save time trying to find out various information on the variety of places in and around UCI in one convenient and up to date application.

Detailed Description of Project Deliverables
We are creating an application, ‘What’s Open Now?’ for the Android platform. The application should be able to provide a list of operational hours for businesses and other places of interest in the specified locations.The application will focus on three areas around UCI: the campus, University Town Center, and the shopping center near Albertson’s. In addition to this, the application should also provide contact information such as addresses, phone numbers, emails, and websites. The application may also include useful relevant information, such as the services that the restaurant or facility offers. 

The application will also be able to use the user’s location and provide contextual information. The application will tell the user what is open around you based upon your phone’s GPS location, within a category of your choosing and time of access. It should be able to determine the user’s location quickly and accurately and notify the user of the hours of operation for places around him or her along with displaying a list of the places that are currently open at that time.  

Characteristics & Requirements of Project Products and Services
The nature of this application is such that one of the main requirements is for the information provided to be constantly updated. The hours of operation, contact information, and locations should always be correct and accurate.

Project Success Criteria
The application should provide accurate and up to date information to the user. The application also needs to be responsive, easy to use, and convenient. Aiming for these qualities will lead to its success as people want an application that makes their lives easier. If the application is out of date, slow, or not user friendly, then it will not be used. The application will also have many different places and have enough locations for it to be useful and justifiable as a stand alone application.

What is Out of Scope
Everything that is outside of the locations mentioned: the UCI campus, University Town Center, and the shopping center off of the intersection of Campus Drive and California Avenue.  Basic contact information will be provided, but more information such as menus for restaurants is out of scope.  For the UCI campus, only eateries, libraries, Aldrich Hall, Zot-n-go, Zot Zone, Campus Police Center, Health Center, and the Visitor Center will be included.

Constraints/Assumptions
There are not many constraints on this project. The projects does assume that there is a need for this application, which we determined through survey of our team members. The project is constrained by the amount of time in this quarter and the lack of a budget. The application is also constrained by the information that is publicly available. That is, if a restaurant for some reason does not give out their telephone number or other basic information, the application will not be able to display that information to the user. In extension, if the information that is publicly available such as on the facility’s website is out of date, then that may cause problems for the application.
